&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Calico (Calico Life Sciences LLC) is an Alphabet-founded research and development company whose mission is to harness advanced technologies and model systems to increase our understanding of the biology that controls human aging. Calico will use that knowledge to devise interventions that enable people to lead longer and healthier lives. Calico’s highly innovative technology labs, its commitment to curiosity-driven discovery science, academic and industry partners, and vibrant drug-development pipeline, together create an inspiring and exciting place to catalyze and enable medical breakthroughs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Description:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Cellular Models and Assay Technologies (CMAT) lab and Microscopy group at Calico are looking for an innovative, technology-driven Scientist to join our teams. This role offers a rare chance to push the boundaries of microscopy and spatial biology within a biotech environment, where novel technologies can be rapidly translated into biological insights that directly inform therapeutic strategy. In collaboration with Biology subject matter experts, the successful candidate will invent, adapt, and apply advanced microscopy techniques to unravel the mechanisms underlying age and age-related disease. A primary area of focus will be the integration of Laser Capture Microdissection (LCM) with proximity biotinylation, in order to map molecular environments within cells and tissues. By combining these with fluorescent biosensors and morphological profiling, you will aim to identify and isolate specific cellular states for deeper phenotyping.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This hands-on role requires deep expertise in Microscopy, Image Analysis, Cell and Tissue Biology, alongside the ability to develop or implement novel methods as needed. This role will evolve as scientific questions demand, and we are looking for a curious, versatile and proactive scientist who takes an active role in the evolution and expansion of their role.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In collaboration with other Microscopy and Image Analysis experts, deploy cutting edge technologies to accelerate diverse projects across Calico&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply Laser Capture Microdissection (LCM) to isolate specific cell populations or morphological features from cell cultures and tissue sections for downstream multiomics analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accelerate LCM workflows through automated image analysis and segmentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and optimize functional reporters in cells and tissues, e.g. proximity biotinylation, to map protein-protein interactions, and fluorescent biosensors to track cellular response to perturbation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously explore this ever-evolving field and invent and/or implement novel systems as they become available&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ph.D. in Cell Biology, Bioengineering, Biophysics, or a related field with 3+ years of post-doctoral or industry experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive hands-on experience with complex fluorescence microscopy techniques (e.g. laser capture microdissection, smart microscopy, light sheet, live cell imaging, super-resolution, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of developing or adapting novel microscopy methods to uncover biological insights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability in quantitative image analysis, utilizing commercial software (e.g., Imaris, Arivis), open-source tools (e.g., FIJI, CellProfiler), and custom solutions (e.g., Python)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with functional reporter systems in cells and/or tissues (e.g., proximity biotinylation, fluorescent biosensors) and demonstrated ability to rapidly adopt new techniques&lt;/li&gt;
